"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-3fb9b3c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"3fb9b3c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-cc88e83\" data-id=\"cc88e83\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-8fa06ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"8fa06ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Acute Colonic Pseudo-Obstruction (Ogilvie\u2019s Syndrome)<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-870298c elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"870298c\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-row\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-5f25df6\" data-id=\"5f25df6\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f8a7cc4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"f8a7cc4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><strong>Basics<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Acute Colonic Dilation in the Absence of Mechanical Obstruction<\/li><li>Mortality Risk: 8%<ul><li>40-45% if Perforated<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>High-Risk for Perforation:<ul><li><strong>Cecum &gt; 10-12 cm<\/strong><\/li><li>Duration &gt; 6 Days<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Risk Factors<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Elderly<\/li><li>Acute Medical Illness \u2013 Infection or Cardiac Disease Most Common<\/li><li>Opiates<\/li><li>Nonoperative Trauma<\/li><li>Surgery \u2013 Cesarean Section &amp; Hip Surgery Most Common<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Presentation<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Abdominal Distention \u2013 Primary Clinical Feature<\/li><li>Abdominal Pain<\/li><li>Nausea &amp; Vomiting<\/li><li>Diarrhea or Constipation<\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Diagnosis<\/strong><\/p><ul><li>Dx: CT<ul><li>Proximal Dilation Extending from the Cecum<\/li><li>Extends to:<ul><li>Hepatic Flexure: 17%<\/li><li>Splenic Flexure: 56%<\/li><li>Left Colon: 27%<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Can Monitor with Abdominal XR \u2013 Nonspecific for Dx<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><p><strong>Treatment<\/strong><\/p><ul><li><strong>&lt; 10-12 cm Diameter: Bowel Rest<\/strong><ul><li>Serial Abdominal Examination &amp; Abdominal XR<\/li><li>Consider Methylnaltrexone (Relistor) if Opiate-Induced<ul><li>GI Tract Specific Opioid Antagonist<\/li><\/ul><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>&gt; 10-12 cm Diameter or Fails After 48-72 Hours: <strong>Neostigmine<\/strong><ul><li>85-90% Success Rate<\/li><li>*Monitor for Bradycardia<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>If Neostigmine Contraindicated or Fails: <strong>Endoscopic Decompression<\/strong><ul><li>May Consider Second Dose of Neostigmine After 24 Hours<\/li><li>Consider Leaving a Tube for Continued Decompression<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>If Endoscopic Decompression Fails: <strong>Cecostomy Tube<\/strong><ul><li>Can Be Performed by Colonoscopy, Interventional Radiology or Surgery<\/li><\/ul><\/li><li>Surgery Indications: Ischemia or Perforation<\/li><\/ul>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-50 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-d8c5c8f\" data-id=\"d8c5c8f\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0002ec4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"0002ec4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\">\n\t\t\t\t<p><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-7782 size-full\" src=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Ogilvies-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Ogilvies-2.jpg 500w, https:\/\/operativereview.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/09\/Ogilvies-2-300x225.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" \/><\/p><p>Ogilvie&#8217;s Syndrome<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-db32021 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"db32021\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-text-editor elementor-clearfix\